This paper deals with data quality management, which is closely related to databases (cs.DB). The paper discusses the complexity and efficient algorithms for optimal subset repair, which is a fundamental computing task and can be seen as a problem in computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also proposes approximation algorithms, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper uses experiments to evaluate the efficiency of their proposed method, which involves data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
